  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis in an OpenType variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

<xref:T:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis> describes a variation axis available in a variable font typeface. Axes are identified by a four-byte tag (e.g., `wght` for weight, `wdth` for width) and have a range of allowed values.

Use <xref:P:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> to retrieve all axes for a given typeface.
]]></format></remarks>
